        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:57PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tomball, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tomball, Pinehurst, Magnolia, Stagecoach, and Hooks Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
